<title>USA: Amway defers offering, sets buyback.</title>
<headline>Amway defers offering, sets buyback.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-03-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Amway Asia Pacific Ltd said Monday its previously announced secondary offering has been deferred and the company has authorized the repurchase of up to 1.25 million of its common shares.</p>
<p>It said the offering was deferred due to current market conditions, adding its currently filed registration statement relating to the offering would be converted into a shelf or continuous offering in order to accommodate one or more sales when market conditions warranted.</p>
<p>((-- New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610.))</p>
